<h2>Features</h2>
- Multi-plataform;<br />
	- Nintendo Wii <sup>[<a href="#note1">1</a>]</sup>;<br />
	- Windows XP;<br />
	- Windows Vista;<br />
	- Windows 7;<br />
	- iOS (iPhone/iPad) <sup>[<a href="#note2">2</a>]</sup>;<br />
	- MacOSX;<br />
	- Linux;<br />
- Operating System Abstraction;<br />
- Timer module;<br />
- File and FileSystem module;<br />
- Package module;<br />
- Sound System module;<br />
	- Sound effects;<br />
	- Music;<br />
- Memory Management module;<br />
- Memory profiler;<br />
- Memory pools;<br />
- Sprite System;<br />
- Basic Scene Graph;<br />
- Particle System;<br />
- Timeline and Keyframe based Animation System (ie. Flash movie clips);<br />
- Cartridge and SaveSystem;<br />
- Localization support;<br />
	- UTF-8 Strings <sup>[<a href="#note4">4</a>]</sup>;<br />
	- Bitmap font system (no support for TrueType/FreeType fonts - see Seed Framework Design Decisions);<br />
- Movie playback module <sup>[<a href="#note3">3</a>]</sup>;<br />
- Input System module;<br />
	- Pointer based input;<br />
	- Joystick based input;<br />
	- Keyboard based input;<br />
- Screen and Viewports manager module;<br />
- Rendering Device modules:<br />
	- OpenGL 1.4;<br />
	- OpenGL ES 1.1;<br />
	- OpenGL ES 2.0 (incoming);<br />
	- OpenGL 2.0 (incoming);<br />
	- DirectX 8.1;<br />
	- DirectX 9.0c (incoming);<br />
- Threads and Mutex;<br />
- Logging;<br />
- Graphical User Interface module;<br />
	- Sprite based Button;<br />
	- Label;<br />
	- Text area;<br />
	- Drag and Drop;<br />
- Listener based Event System;<br />
	- System Events;<br />
	- FileSystem Events;<br />
	- Input Events;<br />
	- GUI Events;<br />
- Background assets loading;<br />
- Resource Manager module;<br />
	- Resource Garbage Collection;<br />
<br />
<br />
<sup><a name="note1">1</a></sup> Nintendo Wii is available to Official Nintendo Licensed Wii Developers. If you want to evaluate Seed Framework for the Wii, you must use Nintendo's third party validation tool to request access to the code. For licensing details, click here.<br />
<br />
<sup><a name="note2">2</a></sup> iPhone need special licensing terms, for details read License.<br />
<br />
<sup><a name="note3">3</a></sup> Currently only supports Theora playback without sound and for Windows, MacOSX and Linux platforms. iPhone M4V implementation in development.<br />
<br />
<sup><a name="note4">4</a></sup> Strings assets are UTF-8, but they are compiled and as a result is generated a character subset table within a 16bit space to be used with texture-based fonts.<br />